resources.string: Audio Feedback adds spoken and audible feedback to Android Wear devices.

Audio Feedback adds spoken feedback for time and notifications. It reads what is currently on the screen in the watch face and notifications and provides additional audio cues. It does not add screen reading functionality to apps. Touching and swiping the screen has the same effect as when Audio Feedback is off. You can also use wrist gestures to navigate. You can use voice actions to call, send texts, and perform other actions.

"Download this app to connect your Android Wear smartwatch with your Android phone. Android Wear watches let you: - Check important info like who’s calling, SMS and messages, and alerts from your favorite apps. You can even speak or draw a quick response right from your watch. - Get built-in fitness monitoring and coaching from your favorite running and fitness apps: Endomondo, Google Fit, Runkeeper, Strava, and more. Track your steps, distance, and calories while you walk, run, or ride your bike. And even measure your heart rate. - Save time with smart help from Google. Get reminders from Google Now about your next appointment, current traffic conditions, flight status, restaurant reservation, and more. Speak “Ok Google” to ask any question you want. - Pursue your passions with Google Maps, Foursquare, Google Play Music, Shazam, WhatsApp, and thousands more of your favorite Android apps. - Express your style with watches like ASUS ZenWatch, Huawei Watch, LG Watch Urbane, Moto 360, Samsung Gear Live, Sony SmartWatch 3, and more. Choose from thousands of watch faces from Android Wear.
Learn more about Android Wear: https://www.android.com/wear Buy an Android Wear watch: https://store.google.com/category/android_wear For a list of known issues and support: https://productforums.google.com/forum/#!forum/android-wear"
